	<annotations>
		<text id="0" rect="(70.0, 62.0, 665.0, 156.0)" font-family="Helvetica" font-size="16">Example of simulating a single X-ray elliptical lens. 
Two interfaces are used: first is plane, and second is elliptical.
Two setups are shown, the first one uses preprocessor data for the refractive index, and the second one has the refraction index as input parameter.
See: https://doi.org/10.1107/S0909049512003020
</text>
		<text id="1" rect="(106.0, 884.0, 150.0, 27.0)" font-family="Helvetica" font-size="16">Collimated beam</text>
		<text id="2" rect="(124.0, 1568.0, 150.0, 27.0)" font-family="Helvetica" font-size="16">Divergent beam</text>
	</annotations>
